title: Expectations low ahead of Obama and Xi Jinping’s cyber-security meeting
text:
US and China are expected to announce a limited agreement to slow hacking attacks, but experts say a wide-ranging settlement is not likely
Hopes of a lasting peace between China and the US over cyber- security were fading in Washington ahead of a crunch dinner between presidents Barack Obama and Xi Jinping on Thursday that is ... »
